-- Pulte posts narrower quarterly loss
-- 
-- Tue May 5, 2009 5:31pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/05/us-pultehomes-idUSTRE5446I720090505

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Pulte Homes Inc ( PHM.N ) on Tuesday reported a narrower first-quarter loss as charges to write down the value of its land declined. 

 The homebuilder posted a net loss of $514.8 million, or $2.02 per share, compared with a loss of $696.1 million, or $2.75 per share, last year. Consolidated revenue fell 59 percent to $587.4 million. Pulte is schedule to acquire rival homebuilder Centex Corp ( CTX.N ) in the third quarter. (Reporting by  Helen Chernikoff ; editing by Carol Bishopric)